<section>
<title>Detailed Description</title>

<para><literallayout><computeroutput>  Base class for servlet
  This is the common behavior between protocols such as HTTP and CSP
  so this is the low-level data methods.

  All servlets support a request, which is a client sending a message to
</computeroutput></literallayout> the server requesting data. In HTTP, a request is ASCII with many potential lines if input, whereas in CSP it is a lot shorter, fixed format, and binary <literallayout><computeroutput>  @author: Dov Kruger
</computeroutput></literallayout> </para>
